## Commands & settings

- `superGit.show`, `superGit.showLogs`, `superGit.toggleDebug`
- `superGit.debug: true` enables debug logs in output channel + log file
- Depends on `vscode.git`; `main` is `./dist/extension.js`

## Git action pitfalls (branch tracking)

- `git pull --ff-only origin <branch>` updates the **checked-out** branch, not `<branch>` when another branch is selected
- Non-checked-out pull: `git fetch <remote> <branch>:<branch>` (fast-forward only; no `+`)
- Checked-out pull: `git pull --ff-only <remote> <branch>`
- After successful branch actions in `runBranchAction`, refresh per `src/extension/refreshPolicy.ts` classifiers:
  - `Promise.all([loadBranches(root), loadRemotes(root, { enrichDefaults })])`
  - Commits: inline `loadCommits` when Graph tab active, else set `commitGraphDirty` + bump epoch
  - Files Diff: inline `loadFilesDiff` when Files Diff tab is active and a comparison is selected
- **`invalidateRemoteDataCaches(root, { defaultBranches? })`** — full invalidation for `fetch`/`prune-stale`/`delete-remote`; list-only (`defaultBranches: false`) for safe actions like `push`/`pull`/`add-upstream`/`set-upstream`/`set-default-upstream`/`checkout-new-local-branch`/`delete`
- **Checkout New Branch** (`checkout-new-local-branch`) is separate from remote-only **Create Local Branch** (`pull` fetch refspec): checkout creates a *new* local branch and switches worktree; pull fast-forwards/creates the selected ref without checkout. Local pill → `git checkout -b <new> <source>`; explicit remote row or remote-only → `git checkout -b <new> --track <remote>/<branch>` after local `refs/remotes/*` exists. Stale remote row (`remoteRefExists === false`) is not a valid remote source — branch from local pill instead.
- **Fetch and Set Upstream** when remote branch exists but not fetched: use explicit refspec `refs/heads/<branch>:refs/remotes/<remote>/<branch>` before `git branch --set-upstream-to` (plain `git fetch remote branch` may only update FETCH_HEAD)
- **Set upstream / Push and Set Upstream:** multi-remote repos use extension-host `showQuickPick` (not manual input); remote branch defaults to local branch name (or explicit `remoteBranchName` from selection)
- **Multi-remote tracking:** Git allows one **default** upstream per branch. `add-upstream` push/fetch adds `refs/remotes/<remote>/<branch>` **without** `-u` or changing default. `set-default-upstream` runs `git branch --set-upstream-to` for a selected existing tracking ref. `getBranches()` already lists all local remote-tracking refs; configured upstream row shows **`default`** badge in Tracking.
- **Prune Stale** clears broken upstream via `unsetStaleUpstreamLinks`; never run cleanup if `refs/remotes/` for-each-ref fails
- Webview must pass explicit `branchName` and `remote` on `execute-branch-action` for Tracking selection
- **Remote-only refs** (on remote, no local branch): `getRemoteBranches()` sets `localBranchName` only when a matching `refs/heads/<name>` exists. `BranchSidebar`, `TrackingView`, and Files Diff must consume `remoteBranches` and show refs where `localBranchName` is unset — not only local rows from `getBranches()`.

## Agent policy

- Read only this repo's guidance; do not import unrelated project memories
- **UI/design specs:** `.cursor/rules/supergit-*.mdc` are canonical; `Design/` may hold exploratory mockups — merge approved behavior into rules before shipping
- Do not infer log events not visible in summaries; add diagnostics instead
- Before claiming refresh/reload fixes, verify log **counts** per `supergit-refresh-coordination.mdc` (not just presence of one skip/coalesce line)
- Search VS Code Server logs narrowly by session and extension name
- Inspect screenshots/images directly; do not guess from filenames
- Do not revert user changes; keep fixes scoped; avoid destructive git commands unless asked
- Prefer `rg` / `rg --files` for search
- **Fix requests:** implement → verify → `npm run package` at **current** `package.json` version → give VSIX path. No commit/push/tag/release unless asked.
- **GA / release:** determine semver bump → changelog → verify → package → commit → push → tag `v<version>` → GitHub release with VSIX (see `supergit-release`).
- **Build/package VSIX only — never install or reload the extension for the user** (see `supergit-build-verify` rule)
- **Version numbers:** read from `package.json` (`"version"`); do not hardcode versions in rules or `AGENTS.md`. VSIX = `supergit-<version>.vsix`; git tag = `v<version>`.
